==English==

===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm|en}} ''hondfast'', past participle of ''[[hondfesten]]'' 'to betroth', from Old Norse ''[[handfesta]]'' 'to strike a bargain, pledge', itself from ''[[hönd]]'' 'hand' + ''[[festa]]'' 'to fasten, fix, affirm' (compare see [[past-]] in Indo-European roots).

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} A [[hold]], grasp; [[custody]], power of confining or keeping.
#: {{rfquotek|Shakespeare}}
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} A [[contract]], agreement, covenant; specifically [[betrothal]], [[espousal]].

